==English==

===Noun phrase===
'''solid phase'''
#{{physics}} One of the three fundamental [[structural]] [[phases]] of matter in which the [[cohesive force]] of matter is strong enough to keep the molecules or atoms in the given positions, restraining the [[thermal mobility]].

====Usage notes====
*The word ''solid phase'' tends to be used when the [[statistical mechanical]] or [[thermodynamic]] nature of matter is focused on rather than the matter itself.

====Synonyms====
*[[solid]]

